  "chapter": {
    "number": 5,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Prayer for Restoration"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remember, O LORD, what has happened to us.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Look and see our disgrace!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Our inheritance has been turned over to strangers,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "our houses to foreigners.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We have become fatherless orphans;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "our mothers are widows.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We must buy the water we drink;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "our wood comes at a price.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We are closely pursued;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we are weary and find no rest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We submitted to Egypt and Assyria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to get enough bread.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Our fathers sinned and are no more,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but we bear their punishment.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Slaves rule over us;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "there is no one to deliver us from their hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "We get our bread at the risk of our lives",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of the sword in the wilderness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Our skin is as hot as an oven",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "with fever from our hunger.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Women have been ravished in Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "virgins in the cities of Judah.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Princes have been hung up by their hands;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "elders receive no respect.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Young men toil at millstones;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "boys stagger under loads of wood.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The elders have left the city gate;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the young men have stopped their music.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Joy has left our hearts;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "our dancing has turned to mourning.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The crown has fallen from our head.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Woe to us, for we have sinned!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because of this, our hearts are faint;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because of these, our eyes grow dimâ€”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "because of Mount Zion, which lies desolate,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "patrolled by foxes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You, O LORD, reign forever;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Your throne endures from generation to generation.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why have You forgotten us forever?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Why have You forsaken us for so long?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Restore us to Yourself, O LORD, so we may return;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "renew our days as of old,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "unless You have utterly rejected us",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and remain angry with us beyond measure.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
